{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"PushManager.permissionState()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/permissionState","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Push_API\">Push API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager\"><code>PushManager</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/supportedContentEncodings\"><code>supportedContentEncodings</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/getSubscription\"><code>getSubscription()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/hasPermission\"><code>hasPermission()</code></a></li><li><em><code>permissionState()</code></em></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/register\"><code>register()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/registrations\"><code>registrations()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/subscribe\"><code>subscribe()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-deprecated\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/unregister\"><code>unregister()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Push API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushEvent\"><code>PushEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushMessageData\"><code>PushMessageData</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushSubscription\"><code>PushSubscription</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerRegistration/pushManager\"><code>ServiceWorkerRegistration.pushManager</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>permissionState()</code></strong> method of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager\"><code>PushManager</code></a> interface returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves to a\n  string indicating the permission state of the push manager. Possible\n  values are <code>'prompt'</code>, <code>'denied'</code>, or <code>'granted'</code>.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>Note:</strong> As of Firefox 44, the permissions for <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Notifications_API\">Notifications</a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Push_API\">Push</a> have been merged. If permission is\n    granted for notifications, push will also be enabled.\n  </p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">permissionState()\npermissionState(options)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      An object containing optional configuration parameters. It can have the following\n      properties:\n    </p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"uservisibleonly\"><code>userVisibleOnly</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A boolean indicating that the returned push\n          subscription will only be used for messages whose effect is made visible to the\n          user.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"applicationserverkey\"><code>applicationServerKey</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A public key your push server will use to\n          send messages to client apps via a push server. This value is part of a signing\n          key pair generated by your application server and usable with elliptic curve\n          digital signature (ECDSA) over the P-256 curve.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that resolves to a string with a value of\n  <code>'prompt'</code>, <code>'denied'</code>, or <code>'granted'</code>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/push-api/#dom-pushmanager-permissionstate","title":"Push API"}],"query":"api.PushManager.permissionState"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.PushManager.permissionState","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/permissionState/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The permissionState() method of the\n  PushManager interface returns a Promise that resolves to a\n  string indicating the permission state of the push manager. Possible\n  values are 'prompt', 'denied', or 'granted'.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T06:09:49.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"PushManager.permissionState()","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/pushmanager/permissionstate","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/pushmanager/permissionstate/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/2b8f5d9a29f00aea5d2edfa78d1fb90c51752858","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager","title":"PushManager"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PushManager/permissionState","title":"PushManager.permissionState()"}],"pageTitle":"PushManager.permissionState() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}